sequenceDiagram
    participant "EMP API Service" as EMPAPIService
    participant "Primary Operational DB" as PrimaryOperationalDB
    participant "Audit & Observability DB" as AuditObservabilityDB

    activate EMPAPIService
    EMPAPIService->>EMPAPIService: 1. 1. [Trigger] ProjectsController receives request to change project status.
    EMPAPIService->>PrimaryOperationalDB: 2. 2. Fetch current project state for validation and snapshot.
    PrimaryOperationalDB-->>EMPAPIService: Returns current project entity.
    EMPAPIService->>EMPAPIService: 3. 3. [Security & Compliance] Validate state transition against business rules.
    EMPAPIService-->>EMPAPIService: Proceeds if valid.
    EMPAPIService->>EMPAPIService: 4. 4. [Audit] Create 'before' state snapshot.
    EMPAPIService->>PrimaryOperationalDB: 5. 5. Update project status within a transaction.
    PrimaryOperationalDB-->>EMPAPIService: Returns success/failure of commit.
    EMPAPIService->>EMPAPIService: 6. 6. [Audit] Construct immutable audit log entry.
    EMPAPIService-->>EMPAPIService: Returns AuditLog object.
    EMPAPIService->>AuditObservabilityDB: 7. 7. [Audit] Write audit log entry to dedicated data store.
    AuditObservabilityDB-->>EMPAPIService: Returns success confirmation.
    EMPAPIService->>EMPAPIService: 8. 8. Return success response to the initiator.
    EMPAPIService-->>EMPAPIService: HTTP 200 OK with updated project DTO.

    note over EMPAPIService: Compliance as Code: The business logic in Step 3 is a direct implementation of 'Compliance as Cod...
    note over AuditObservabilityDB: Data Immutability: The OpenSearch index for audit logs must have a policy that denies update and ...
    note over EMPAPIService: Transactional Consistency: The business rule 'audit log write must succeed for the entire operati...

    deactivate EMPAPIService
